  "texts": [
    "Here are some frequently used datasets in the context of GANs.",
    "• MNIST:Description: A series of 28 × 28 grayscale photos of handwritten numerals (0-9).",
    "Due to its simplicity and modest size, this dataset is frequently used as a benchmark for GANs in practice.• CIFAR 10 and CIFAR 100:CIFAR-10 has 60,000 32x32 color pictures divided into 10 classes, and CIFAR-100 includes 100 classes.Use Case: Widely used for GANs that operate with color photos and other complicated visual information.• ImageNet:A large-scale collection with over a million tagged high-resolution photos from 1,000 distinct categories.Use Case: Commonly used to train GANs on a wide range of complicated real-world pictures.• CelebA: This dataset includes over 200,000 celebrity photos with annotations on different characteristics.",
    "Use Case: Frequently used for face-related GAN applications, such as facial attribute modification and creation.• LSUN (Large Scale Scene Understanding) Dataset: Description: A collection of scene-centric photos from many categories, including bedrooms, churches, and bridges.",
    "Use Case: Suitable for GANs that generate realistic sceneries and backdrops.• DeepFashion: This dataset has over 800,000 varied fashion photos with thorough annotations."
  ],
